CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 12, 1956, pg. 20, reads: "College Fund Drive Begins - The United Negro College Fund luncheon opened the drive to raise $63,000 for this district. Attending the luncheon were, left to right: Ernest T. Weir, president of the National Steel Co.; Robert Fay, of the Pittsburgh Plate Glass Co.; Dr. Hollis Price, president of LeMoyne College; J. A. Appleton, vice president of the Pennsylvania Railroad, and the Rev. William J. Harvey III, pastor of Macedonia Baptist Church. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of men seated behind banquet table, from left: Ernest T. Weir, Robert Fay, Hollis Price, J. A. Appleton, and Rev. William J. Harvey III, at United Negro College Fund luncheon in interior with abstract patterned curtain
